"It is also the best method in the absence of regular access to the population, and if the latter must travel to central locations. In such cases, it is best to combine registration with the fi rst food distribution in order to spare recipients unnecessary journeys. In 1985 in Ethiopia, some groups undertook journeys of several days on foot in order to be registered and receive their rations. Census locations must be large enough to accommodate considerable numbers of individuals comfortably, and to enable them to commute unhindered between entry and exit points."